            "id": "4575136",
            "title": "Aurora Cannabis acquires Safari Flower Company for C$26.5M",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Aurora Cannabis (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ACB\" title=\"Aurora Cannabis Inc.\">ACB</a></span>) has acquired Safari Flower Company for about C$26.5M, including up to C$2M in contingent cash payments.</p>\n<p>As consideration on closing, Aurora issued the selling shareholder 2,417,180 common shares and paid the selling shareholder C$15M in cash, subject to customary adjustments post-closing.</p>\n<p>Safari Flower’s 59,000-square-foot EU GMP-certified indoor cultivation and manufacturing facility in Ontario, Canada, will provide Aurora Cannabis (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ACB\" title=\"Aurora Cannabis Inc.\">ACB</a>) with incremental capacity that is closely aligned with its existing cultivation and manufacturing sites.</p>\n<p>The increased capacity will be used to supply EU GMP flower to Aurora's key international markets, including Germany, Australia, Poland, and the UK, and support further market expansion.</p>\n<p>This transaction is expected to deliver positive adjusted EBITDA contributions in fiscal year 2027, with incremental benefits in fiscal year 2028 and beyond.</p>\n<p>Source: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20473655-aurora-cannabis-accelerates-global-medical-cannabis-leadership-with-accretive-acquisition-of\">Press Release</a></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4575136-aurora-cannabis-acquires-safari-flower-company-for-c265m",
            "pub_date": "2026-04-15 19:22:01",
            "source": "seekalpha",
