            "id": "4575139",
            "title": "Mortgage demand rises as rates fall amid the evolving situation in the Middle East",
            "description": "<html><body><ul> <li><a href=\"https://www.mba.org/news-and-research/newsroom?utm_source=featured-menu&amp;utm_medium=newslink-website&amp;utm_campaign=menu&amp;utm_content=newsroom\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">MBA Mortgage Applications</a></li> <li>Composite Index: +1.8% to 281.0, compared to -0.8% to 276.0 in the prior week.</li> <li>Purchase Index: -1.0% to 159.5, vs. +1.1% to 161.1 a week ago.</li> <li>Refinance Index: +5.1% to 966.8, vs. -2.8% to 919.9 in the prior week.</li> <li>30-year fixed-rate mortgages came in at 6.42%, compared to 6.51% last week.</li>\n<li>\"Given the evolving situation in the Middle East and its impact on energy and commodity prices, mortgage rates declined last week,\" said Mortgage Bankers Association Economist Joel Kan.</li>\n<li>\"Purchase activity remained subdued as potential homebuyers remained hesitant given the current economic uncertainty, which kept purchase applications below last year's level for the second consecutive week,\" said Kan.</li> </ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder_news_bottom\"></div></body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
