            "title": "Bank of America GAAP EPS of $1.11 beats by $0.09, revenue of $30.3B beats by $350M",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Bank of America <a href=\"https://d1io3yog0oux5.cloudfront.net/_d4ae35015e306c7913d07024bace714a/bankofamerica/db/806/10536/earnings_release/The+Press+Release_1Q26.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BAC\" title=\"Bank of America Corporation\">BAC</a></span>): Q1 GAAP EPS of $1.11 <span> beats by $0.09</span>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $30.3B (+10.7% Y/Y) <span> beats by $350M</span>.</li>\n<li>Revenue, net of interest expense, of $30.3 billion ($30.4 billionFTE),(<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/A\" title=\"Agilent Technologies, Inc.\">A</a>) up 7%, reflected higher net interest income (NII), sales andtrading revenue, asset management fees and investment banking fees</li>\n<li>NII of $15.7 billion ($15.9 billion FTE),(<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/A\" title=\"Agilent Technologies, Inc.\">A</a>) up 9%, driven by higher NIIrelated to Global Markets activity, higher deposit and loan balances,and fixed-rate asset repricing, partially offset by the impact of lowerinterest rates</li>\n<li>Provision for credit losses of $1.3 billion decreased from $1.5 billionin 1Q25 and was relatively flat to 4Q25</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
